---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog - Total Impact">
  <main class="blog-page">
    <!-- Header Navigation -->
    <header class="header">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="header-content">
          <a href="/" class="logo">
            <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Total Impact" />
          </a>
          <nav class="header-nav">
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <a href="#about">About</a>
            <a href="#services">Services</a>
            <a href="#portfolio">Portfolio</a>
            <a href="/blog" class="active">Blog</a>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Blog Content -->
    <article class="blog-article">
      <div class="container">
        <!-- Hero Image -->
        <div class="blog-hero">
          <img src="/images/blog-hero.jpg" alt="Community impact work in action" />
        </div>

        <!-- Article Header -->
        <header class="article-header">
          <h1>Why We Do What We Do</h1>
          <div class="article-meta">
            <time datetime="2024-12-25">December 25, 2024</time>
          </div>
        </header>

        <!-- Article Content -->
        <div class="article-content">
          <p>At Total Impact, our work begins with a question: what does real, measurable change look like for people and the planet? In the rapidly evolving development sector, too many organizations struggle to show—not just promise—the impact they create. Impact data gets trapped in spreadsheets, jargon, and silos, missing an opportunity to build trust, inspire partners, and unlock new funding.</p>

          <p>We believe that impact should be at the heart of every organization's strategy—not an afterthought or a report filed away at year's end. That's why we empower teams to measure, manage, and communicate their social and environmental outcomes clearly, credibly, and compellingly.</p>

          <h2>Our approach is simple:</h2>

          <p>We use global frameworks like IRIS+ and the SDGs, but always tailor them to local realities and lived experience.</p>

          <p>We help organizations move beyond numbers, translating complex data into stories that matter to funders, customers, and most importantly, communities.</p>

          <p>Our team brings together over a decade of experience across education, livelihoods, sustainability, gender, and grassroots development, building systems and narratives that help organizations scale their impact.</p>

          <h2>We do this work because we have seen, firsthand, the power of transparent, well-communicated impact:</h2>

          <ul>
            <li>Livelihoods created and tracked.</li>
            <li>Sustainability outcomes that aren't just claimed, but demonstrated.</li>
            <li>Campaigns that meet people where they are, with compassion and clarity.</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Our goal is to help purpose-driven organizations lead with their values—and prove their value. We believe that when impact is measurable, visible, and understood, it becomes a catalyst for growth, resilience, and real-world change.</p>

          <p><strong>This is why we do what we do. And we're excited to walk this path with partners who share our vision: impact as the new bottom line—for everyone.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Back to Home Button -->
        <div class="article-footer">
          <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to Home</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .blog-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--background);
  }

  .header {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.95);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    z-index: 1000;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .header-content {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .logo img {
    height: 40px;
    width: auto;
  }

  .header-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .header-nav a {
    color: var(--white);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: var(--transition);
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .header-nav a:hover,
  .header-nav a.active {
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }

  .header-nav a::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 0;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .header-nav a:hover::after,
  .header-nav a.active::after {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .blog-article {
    padding-top: 100px;
  }

  .blog-hero {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }

  .blog-hero img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .article-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .article-meta {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .article-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .article-content p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .article-content ul {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .article-content li {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .article-content strong {
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }

  .article-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: var(--white);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: var(--transition);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .btn::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: -100%;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2), transparent);
    transition: var(--transition);
  }

  .btn:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0, 174, 239, 0.3);
  }

  .btn:hover::before {
    left: 100%;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .header-content {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .header-nav {
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .blog-article {
      padding-top: 120px;
    }

    .blog-hero img {
      height: 250px;
    }

    .article-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .article-content {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    .article-content p,
    .article-content li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .article-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Header scroll effect
  window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
    const header = document.querySelector('.header');
    if (header) {
      const scrolled = window.scrollY > 50;
      header.style.background = scrolled ? 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.98)' : 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.95)';
    }
  });

  // Smooth scrolling for anchor links
  document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
    anchor.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const href = this.getAttribute('href');
      if (href) {
        const target = document.querySelector(href);
        if (target) {
          const headerHeight = document.querySelector('.header')?.offsetHeight || 0;
          const targetPosition = target.offsetTop - headerHeight;
          
          window.scrollTo({
            top: targetPosition,
            behavior: 'smooth'
          });
        }
      }
    });
  });
</script>
</Layout>